1
00:00:04,675 --> 00:00:07,315
Where do all of these sentiments come from?

2
00:00:07,706 --> 00:00:11,486
They want to express, you know, some sort of eternal dance,

3
00:00:11,507 --> 00:00:15,287
an eternal night, eternal love. Why?

4
00:00:15,863 --> 00:00:19,993
Do we think, oh, that’s just sentiment?

5
00:00:20,043 --> 00:00:23,473
No, it’s the real innate sentiment of the soul.

6
00:00:23,495 --> 00:00:25,455
It’s what the soul is hankering for —

7
00:00:25,483 --> 00:00:30,623
the eternal night, the eternal love, the eternal dance.

8
00:00:31,014 --> 00:00:33,584
It’s the rasa-dance.

9
00:00:35,978 --> 00:00:41,568
Everybody — theist, agnostic, atheist.

10
00:00:41,902 --> 00:00:46,852
Guru Mahārāj used to say, “No one can seriously deny

11
00:00:46,877 --> 00:00:50,027
that they don’t want to be happy,

12
00:00:50,049 --> 00:00:51,959
that they’re not searching for happiness”.

13
00:00:51,980 --> 00:00:56,605
ramante yogino ’nante
satyānande cid-ātmani
(Padma Purāṇa)
 

14
00:00:56,751 --> 00:01:00,751
The yogis, they’re experiencing a pleasure

15
00:01:01,643 --> 00:01:07,583
that is higher than the sort of pleasure

16
00:01:07,621 --> 00:01:12,621
that one experiences in this world from erotic sensual activity.

17
00:01:13,226 --> 00:01:15,166
The brahmanandees.

18
00:01:15,272 --> 00:01:18,252
They experience the pleasure of Brahmananda

19
00:01:18,320 --> 00:01:21,600
ten million times greater than sensuous pleasure.

20
00:01:21,674 --> 00:01:27,504
If you multiply the pleasure of Brahmananda a trillion fold

21
00:01:27,643 --> 00:01:33,103
it’s not equivalent to a drop of the pleasure of Kṛṣṇa-bhakti.

22
00:01:33,381 --> 00:01:35,441
That’s a statement from Rūpa Goswāmī.

23
00:01:35,600 --> 00:01:40,590
The senses, the mind, the intelligence, according to Guru Mahārāj,

24
00:01:40,617 --> 00:01:47,547
all shadow representations of the spiritual aspect of the same.

25
00:01:48,158 --> 00:01:50,178
And that will be achieved through

26
00:01:50,202 --> 00:01:54,292
freedom for the senses or freedom from the senses?

27
00:01:54,831 --> 00:01:57,110
So in Bhagavad-gītā here Kṛṣṇa says,

28
00:01:57,110 --> 00:02:01,340
bhūmir āpo ’nalo vāyuḥ
khaṁ mano buddhir eva ca
 

29
00:02:01,362 --> 00:02:05,362
ahaṅkāra itīyaṁ me
bhinnā prakṛtir aṣṭadhā
(Bhagavad-gītā 7.4)
 

30
00:02:05,612 --> 00:02:09,492
Earth, water, fire, air, ether, mind, intelligence and ego,

31
00:02:09,519 --> 00:02:14,269
He said, “these are My inferior energy”.

32
00:02:16,964 --> 00:02:20,684
Then He said, and that’s so — mind, intelligence — inferior,

33
00:02:20,686 --> 00:02:22,046
and jīva-bhutah:

34
00:02:22,896 --> 00:02:26,976
apareyam itas tv anyāṁ
prakṛtiṁ viddhi me parām
(Bhagavad-gītā 7.5)
 

35
00:02:27,407 --> 00:02:32,837
jīva is a para-prakriti — superior energy to all of those things.

36
00:02:33,465 --> 00:02:37,775
Without controlled senses there’s no question of spontaneous love.

37
00:02:38,026 --> 00:02:43,016
We’ll project that our experience of mundane love

38
00:02:43,402 --> 00:02:46,122
we’ll project that |as being|,

39
00:02:46,142 --> 00:02:52,387
we’ll impose that idea on spontaneous love of rāga-bhaktas

40
00:02:52,388 --> 00:02:55,518
and that’s an offense against divinity

41
00:02:55,538 --> 00:02:58,608
to think these pastimes are mundane,

42
00:02:58,633 --> 00:03:00,933
like the mundane affairs between men and women.

43
00:03:00,983 --> 00:03:08,493
So that means the mundane mind, the mundane intelligence, these mundane elements,

44
00:03:08,553 --> 00:03:13,219
they’re covering jīva

45
00:03:14,445 --> 00:03:18,595
but jīva and her pristine glory

46
00:03:19,073 --> 00:03:23,423
has mind, intelligent, senses, everything.

47
00:03:23,934 --> 00:03:29,454
The stranglehold that the mundane erotic principle has upon the heart

48
00:03:29,584 --> 00:03:35,954
can only be broken by the Beauty, Charm and Sweetness of Kṛṣṇa conception

49
00:03:36,591 --> 00:03:39,181
and that is very good news for us

50
00:03:39,215 --> 00:03:45,595
that the original cause of everything is Ecstasy personified,

51
00:03:46,582 --> 00:03:55,542
is loving and affectionate and full of ecstatic happiness,

52
00:03:55,567 --> 00:03:58,247
ever-expanding ever-increasing happiness.

53
00:03:58,304 --> 00:04:01,304
And that we connect with that. What we’ve been told,

54
00:04:01,313 --> 00:04:06,243
hṛṣīkeṇa hṛṣīkeśa-sevanaṁ bhaktir ucyate
(Nārada-pañcarātra)
 

55
00:04:06,631 --> 00:04:11,701
by engaging the senses in the service of Kṛṣṇa.

56
00:04:12,900 --> 00:04:18,760
That will awaken

57
00:04:18,782 --> 00:04:21,542
their natural serving tendency

58
00:04:21,572 --> 00:04:28,472
so that the mundane aspect gradually vanishes — diminishes and vanishes altogether —

59
00:04:28,504 --> 00:04:32,834
and the spiritual golden self comes out.

60
00:04:33,242 --> 00:04:37,822
Then from that position dhīra — undisturbed, no-sense-disturbance.

61
00:04:37,870 --> 00:04:44,000
Then when they hear the divine pastimes of Rādhārāṇī, Kṛṣṇa and Brajagopis

62
00:04:44,920 --> 00:04:50,891
that will awaken spontaneous love, loving sentiments within them.

63
00:04:51,059 --> 00:04:55,469
There’s a local view, local eye, local provincial way of seeing things

64
00:04:55,489 --> 00:04:59,629
and a way of tracing everything to the central conception of the Infinite.

65
00:05:00,345 --> 00:05:06,945
The ultimate adjustment, the big picture, the vision of the mahā-bhāgavata

66
00:05:07,717 --> 00:05:10,067
when līlā is factored in.

67
00:05:10,183 --> 00:05:15,543
Even the deluding of the jīvas is a pastime of Kṛṣṇa.

68
00:05:15,933 --> 00:05:19,933
Someone says, well, why not make another kind of pastime

69
00:05:20,296 --> 00:05:25,266
for them, for these jīvas, where they don’t have to suffer like this.

70
00:05:26,633 --> 00:05:30,633
And one of the answers given is, well, look at the other pastimes —

71
00:05:30,700 --> 00:05:32,170
they’re also suffering.

72
00:05:32,313 --> 00:05:36,906
All suffering is due to separation from Kṛṣṇa, all suffering,

73
00:05:36,906 --> 00:05:40,706
whether it’s the suffering of the conditioned souls

74
00:05:40,822 --> 00:05:47,642
or the anguish of separation experienced in the hearts of the Brajagopis.

75
00:05:47,926 --> 00:05:52,356
The cause of all suffering is |being| separation from Kṛṣṇa.

76
00:05:52,471 --> 00:05:58,181
Yashoda is suffering in separation from Kṛṣṇa, brajagopis are suffering in separation,

77
00:05:58,953 --> 00:06:00,385
Pandavas are suffering.

78
00:06:00,435 --> 00:06:03,525
There’s so much suffering in these different pastimes.

79
00:06:03,585 --> 00:06:12,975
That means then we can’t carry a stereotype of what is happiness into the spiritual domain.

80
00:06:13,502 --> 00:06:17,512
The common stereotype about spiritual culture

81
00:06:17,679 --> 00:06:21,439
is that the spiritual person is always smiling

82
00:06:21,927 --> 00:06:23,537
and like happy Buddha.

83
00:06:23,661 --> 00:06:28,941
Consciousness can feel the full spectral range of emotions —

84
00:06:29,292 --> 00:06:34,052
happiness, pleasure, joy, ecstasy, love, affection

85
00:06:34,644 --> 00:06:36,684
but then we have to also acknowledge

86
00:06:36,704 --> 00:06:44,974
it also allows me to feel sad or unhappy, pain, suffering.

87
00:06:45,467 --> 00:06:52,087
The agony of separation from Kṛṣṇa is a liberating type suffering.

88
00:06:52,205 --> 00:06:56,005
Remember, Kṛṣṇa consciousness is about the search for Śrī Kṛṣṇa.

89
00:06:56,094 --> 00:06:59,674
We wonder why Kṛṣṇa is not revealing Himself to me.

90
00:06:59,789 --> 00:07:02,169
I’ve been here for a long time.

91
00:07:03,182 --> 00:07:05,112
Seems like forever.

92
00:07:07,585 --> 00:07:10,815
Doesn’t He get it I’m his devotee?

93
00:07:11,246 --> 00:07:14,056
I was pretty concentrated there for a little while.

94
00:07:14,110 --> 00:07:19,460
Ten million lifetimes of doing the right thing won’t give you this.

95
00:07:19,892 --> 00:07:20,922
That’s amazing!

96
00:07:21,103 --> 00:07:23,683
Even the brajagopis are searching for Kṛṣṇa.

97
00:07:23,945 --> 00:07:25,815
That brings out the best in them.

98
00:07:26,013 --> 00:07:30,283
If this is about achieving the greatest depth of heart

99
00:07:30,309 --> 00:07:34,869
and magnitude of heart and intensity that in separation

100
00:07:34,979 --> 00:07:39,315
a greater depth and magnitude and intensity of heart

101
00:07:39,397 --> 00:07:42,177
is achieved than in Union.

102
00:07:42,387 --> 00:07:46,177
And Gurudev said, “Even the animals know about Union”.

103
00:07:46,593 --> 00:07:49,703
He said, “Goats they understand something about Union”.

104
00:07:49,983 --> 00:07:54,053
He said, “But who understands the peculiar joy of separation?

105
00:07:54,270 --> 00:07:56,170
Not the animals certainly”.

106
00:07:56,553 --> 00:08:00,533
Guru Mahārāj liked to quote the poet Shelley who said:

107
00:08:00,809 --> 00:08:08,689
“Our sweetest songs are those / That tell the saddest tales”.

108
00:08:09,327 --> 00:08:16,877
Heartbreaking love songs, heartbreaking love stories.

109
00:08:17,429 --> 00:08:25,709
Some ladies, for example, were watching heartbreaking love story —

110
00:08:26,096 --> 00:08:28,736
say a little group they’re watching a heartbreaking love story.

111
00:08:29,624 --> 00:08:34,044
Crying. See all are crying, some tissues.

112
00:08:35,891 --> 00:08:40,191
And some man enters the room, seeing them all crying,

113
00:08:40,298 --> 00:08:43,968
thinks, “Oh, let me put on another movie. Watch something…”

114
00:08:44,016 --> 00:08:45,946
They go, “No, don’t touch it”.

115
00:08:47,937 --> 00:08:49,087
Why?

116
00:08:50,216 --> 00:08:53,686
They’re crying and suffering, their hearts are breaking

117
00:08:54,073 --> 00:08:56,643
by watching this but they can’t stop watching.

118
00:08:58,585 --> 00:09:00,695
Because it’s another type of joy,

119
00:09:03,604 --> 00:09:08,054
and deeper than the smiley kind.

120
00:09:08,754 --> 00:09:13,724
How to go on in the absence of Kṛṣṇa?

121
00:09:15,137 --> 00:09:21,737
And interestingly this is the very, very high subject matter

122
00:09:22,554 --> 00:09:25,764
of the depths of separation expressed there

123
00:09:25,784 --> 00:09:30,934
in the conclusion of Śikṣāṣṭakam, the conclusion of Śrī Chaitanya-charitāmṛta —

124
00:09:31,374 --> 00:09:33,444
very, very high and deep things.

125
00:09:33,917 --> 00:09:36,327
But miraculously, mysteriously

126
00:09:36,353 --> 00:09:43,253
it’s also relevant to those in the aspiring position.

127
00:09:44,630 --> 00:09:46,090
Adarśana —

128
00:09:46,125 --> 00:09:51,145
how to pursue Kṛṣṇa consciousness in the apparent absence of Kṛṣṇa,

129
00:09:51,208 --> 00:09:53,968
in the apparent absence of Kṛṣṇa consciousness.

130
00:09:54,443 --> 00:09:56,223
It’s the critical points.

131
00:09:56,465 --> 00:09:57,695
Crude example.

132
00:09:58,118 --> 00:10:01,348
Sometimes people do this in playing with children.

133
00:10:02,552 --> 00:10:05,142
Lovers might even do it but let’s stick with children.

134
00:10:05,461 --> 00:10:08,331
They’ve put them temporarily into some anxiety.

135
00:10:09,150 --> 00:10:12,170
Like a naughty uncle or something.

136
00:10:12,207 --> 00:10:15,897
They hide and the kid, “Ahhh!” And then they go, “See, I’m here!”

137
00:10:18,928 --> 00:10:29,408
They want to see them in that intense state of desperation.

138
00:10:29,664 --> 00:10:32,554
That’s the real test for devotees.

139
00:10:32,932 --> 00:10:35,792
Why is Kṛṣṇa [not] revealing Himself to me?

140
00:10:37,356 --> 00:10:38,706
And Viśvānath says,

141
00:10:38,985 --> 00:10:43,425
“Actually He could but He knows you’re capable of more.

142
00:10:45,841 --> 00:10:48,851
And He knows the heart that you have —

143
00:10:49,944 --> 00:10:51,744
your real heart, your full heart —

144
00:10:51,806 --> 00:10:53,296
it’s capable of so much

145
00:10:54,446 --> 00:10:58,986
that He’s holding back to get you to go to that deeper region of heart.

146
00:11:00,353 --> 00:11:04,353
Because He’s bhāva-grahi-janārdana, bhāva consumer.

147
00:11:04,913 --> 00:11:08,013
He knows your real heart but it’s on a deeper level

148
00:11:08,185 --> 00:11:11,535
and He’s tempted to accept what you’re giving now

149
00:11:11,564 --> 00:11:15,054
but going to hold off and wait for the real stuff —

150
00:11:15,920 --> 00:11:19,210
the deep heart connection, the deep heart’s core —

151
00:11:19,500 --> 00:11:21,510
what will be expressed from there.

152
00:11:21,763 --> 00:11:24,393
Guru Mahārāj said, “If you can be honest

153
00:11:24,466 --> 00:11:29,156
and acknowledge your lack of Kṛṣṇa consciousness,

154
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:32,680
that you have no devotion,

155
00:11:32,959 --> 00:11:36,669
hankering means you’re separated

156
00:11:36,882 --> 00:11:39,722
from the that object for which you hanker

157
00:11:39,963 --> 00:11:43,233
but you have no other shelter,

158
00:11:43,902 --> 00:11:46,772
he said, then you just might be a devotee.

159
00:11:47,122 --> 00:11:50,972
That hunger it’s the purchase price of Kṛṣṇa consciousness.”

160
00:11:51,157 --> 00:11:58,107
So when Kṛṣṇa He gets this inspiration to enjoy in a particular way,

161
00:11:58,535 --> 00:12:05,315
the Yogamaya and Baladeva they’re casting and scripting Kṛṣṇa-līlā.

162
00:12:05,493 --> 00:12:09,683
Casting means selecting who will participate in these pastimes.

163
00:12:09,946 --> 00:12:14,386
So he’s saying when Yogamaya and Baladeva are getting the indication

164
00:12:14,631 --> 00:12:16,781
that Krishna’s to enjoy in this way

165
00:12:18,351 --> 00:12:21,911
they round up these gopis and they say,

166
00:12:22,276 --> 00:12:30,186
“These are qualified to participate now, this one maybe next time, this one a little bit longer.”

167
00:12:30,524 --> 00:12:34,294
Saying just like… And we’ve done it with either mangoes or other fruits.

168
00:12:34,331 --> 00:12:43,251
You put them in a place where they can get heat and light and achieve maturity or fully ripen.

169
00:12:44,330 --> 00:12:47,620
So what is the equivalent of that, the parallel?

170
00:12:48,017 --> 00:12:54,967
Is separation — the fire, the heat of separation so some cannot go.

171
00:12:55,862 --> 00:12:58,772
We’re told everything is significant so it’s said,

172
00:12:58,805 --> 00:13:01,215
“Kṛṣṇa sounds His flute, they start going,

173
00:13:01,235 --> 00:13:04,545
some, we’re told, they’re going so fast —

174
00:13:04,570 --> 00:13:08,760
half dressed, one earring, things on the wrong side —

175
00:13:08,788 --> 00:13:10,318
they’re running to Kṛṣṇa.”

176
00:13:10,885 --> 00:13:17,075
You can imagine if after millions of lifetimes and pursuing Kṛṣṇa consciousness

177
00:13:17,259 --> 00:13:19,279
you get this call:

178
00:13:19,869 --> 00:13:24,069
this is going to be your first encounter with Kṛṣṇa,

179
00:13:24,245 --> 00:13:27,595
you might be a little beside yourself.

180
00:13:29,297 --> 00:13:31,317
So anyway, they’re going… But then we’re told,

181
00:13:31,367 --> 00:13:34,487
“and some they’re pulling babies off their breasts,

182
00:13:34,512 --> 00:13:38,952
the ovens are burning, their husbands and fathers are trying to stop [them]”.

183
00:13:39,099 --> 00:13:40,759
But some are stopped.

184
00:13:42,134 --> 00:13:44,744
That’s also hard to accommodate.

185
00:13:44,872 --> 00:13:50,942
You mean, after millions and millions of lifetimes, finally, the call comes for this type of sevā,

186
00:13:51,527 --> 00:13:52,877
and you can’t go?

187
00:13:53,191 --> 00:13:55,031
So what does that do to them?

188
00:13:55,069 --> 00:13:59,069
That puts them into a deep condition of separation.

189
00:13:59,113 --> 00:14:02,713
It generates the fire and heat of separation,

190
00:14:03,217 --> 00:14:05,577
and it’s the arrangement of Yogamaya because they,

191
00:14:05,595 --> 00:14:10,825
for some reason, they weren’t hundred percent qualified at that point.

192
00:14:11,214 --> 00:14:14,514
So, by getting the call and not being able to go,

193
00:14:14,933 --> 00:14:21,973
the fire and heat of separation will bring them to the mature condition

194
00:14:21,984 --> 00:14:23,454
and they’ll go at another time.

195
00:14:23,594 --> 00:14:28,544
So the heart will be drawn into that plane by affections force —

196
00:14:28,644 --> 00:14:30,994
śrī kṛṣṇa karṣiṇī chasa.

197
00:14:31,265 --> 00:14:35,145
This whole big buildup in the Bhāgavatam to the rasa-līlā.

198
00:14:35,353 --> 00:14:39,353
And no sooner does it begin than it stops.

199
00:14:40,089 --> 00:14:40,919
Why?

200
00:14:41,919 --> 00:14:46,279
It’s just starting and then Kṛṣṇa is gone searching for Rādhārāṇī.

201
00:14:47,604 --> 00:14:48,694
Everything stopped.

202
00:14:49,007 --> 00:14:53,347
And then you would think if you know something about Gaudia ontology then you could say,

203
00:14:53,804 --> 00:15:03,794
“Oh, wait, later we hear: one Kṛṣṇa for every two gopis feeling that one Kṛṣṇa for every gopi through prakash, villas, expansions.

204
00:15:04,062 --> 00:15:10,862
Why didn’t He just expand Himself for everybody and then go run after Rādhārāṇī?

205
00:15:11,155 --> 00:15:15,575
He could do that too. But that’s not what He does. Right?

206
00:15:15,654 --> 00:15:18,714
They’re plunged into an ocean of separation.

207
00:15:19,503 --> 00:15:22,963
How heartbreaking! You’ve made it to the rasa-līlā

208
00:15:23,001 --> 00:15:25,661
and now it’s stopped before it started?

209
00:15:26,597 --> 00:15:28,997
It starts and Kṛṣṇa’s gone?

210
00:15:30,047 --> 00:15:35,137
Is that some kind of a trick or cruel thing to do?

211
00:15:35,292 --> 00:15:42,322
Maybe in some instances after millions and millions of lifetimes, millions of creations

212
00:15:42,337 --> 00:15:45,857
they’ve made it to that point and Kṛṣṇa vanishes?

213
00:15:46,234 --> 00:15:51,094
What kind of Lord are we searching for?

214
00:15:51,501 --> 00:15:54,831
This is the mystery of Kṛṣṇa consciousness,

215
00:15:55,086 --> 00:15:57,306
it’s the mystery of the pastimes of Kṛṣṇa,

216
00:15:57,484 --> 00:15:59,474
it’s the mystery of Kṛṣṇa culture.

217
00:15:59,564 --> 00:16:06,104
It's that the greatest substance of Kṛṣṇa consciousness will be mined in separation.

218
00:16:06,463 --> 00:16:09,443
When someone’s before you, you see them,

219
00:16:09,475 --> 00:16:11,885
they’re not so much in your heart and mind.

220
00:16:13,569 --> 00:16:15,449
You’re looking at their form, seeing them.

221
00:16:15,486 --> 00:16:19,736
But in their absence they’re fully present in your heart and mind.

222
00:16:20,362 --> 00:16:23,992
And what’s Śrīla Guru Mahārāj coined the original phrase

223
00:16:24,039 --> 00:16:26,059
“Union in Separation”.

224
00:16:26,901 --> 00:16:29,661
And separation there can also be union.

225
00:16:29,769 --> 00:16:34,769
If what makes Kṛṣṇa happy is breaking my heart then that’s my happiness.

226
00:16:35,385 --> 00:16:38,765
So how will we understand what is spiritual?

227
00:16:38,910 --> 00:16:40,130
Kavirāj Goswāmī says:

228
00:16:40,188 --> 00:16:47,728
bāhye viṣa-jvālā haya, bhitare ānanda-maya,
kṛṣṇa-premāra adbhuta carita
(Śrī Chaitanya-charitāmṛta, Madhya 2.50)
 

229
00:16:47,949 --> 00:16:56,509
The adbhuta carita or astonishingly wonderful characteristic of Kṛṣṇa-prema is that:

230
00:16:56,729 --> 00:17:00,969
externally it appears like one is suffering like anything

231
00:17:01,179 --> 00:17:06,309
while internally they’re relishing some sort of ecstatic joy.

232
00:17:07,044 --> 00:17:08,704
Viśvanāth says, “Kṛṣṇa’s saying,

233
00:17:08,714 --> 00:17:14,744
‘if at that time when there at the depths of separation, the peak of that longing and hankering,

234
00:17:15,859 --> 00:17:19,799
if I then appear then we’ll have a rasa-līlā’.

235
00:17:20,227 --> 00:17:21,567
That’s what He’s thinking”.

236
00:17:21,887 --> 00:17:23,917
People say, “Well these are very high things”.

237
00:17:23,967 --> 00:17:28,237
Oh, yeah, right, the very high thing is called Kṛṣṇa consciousness.

238
00:17:29,737 --> 00:17:32,817
It’s a very high thing. It’s the most high thing.

239
00:17:33,025 --> 00:17:36,105
It’s the greatest type of happiness.

